gomodel:SYNGO_1145  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099699 replaced by GO:0097060" , "Rationale: Butz et al report in this paper that synaptotagmin VI is localized at synaptic plasma membranes.\nThe authors generate a specific antibody and verify it by using brain material from a synaptotagmin VI KO mouse (unpublished). Immunoblotting of fractions derived from rat brain subcellular fractionation experiments shows no enrichment of synaptogmin VI (though remaining detectable) in synaptic vesicle fractions. In contrast, the protein is evenly detected in all subcellular fractions (Fig. 6).\nAdditionally, in order to test whether synaptotagmin VI is a SV protein, the authors immunoblot ([125]I-secondary-antibody-detection) synaptosomes, crude SV fraction and CPG-isolated SVs for a set of vesicular proteins and observe decrease in synaptotagmin VI signal compared to that of the other SV marker proteins, e.g. synaptogyrin I, which is used for normalization (Fig. 7).\nSynaptic vesicle immunoisolation via anti-synaptotagmin-1 or anti-synaptobrevin 2 antibodies and immunodetection (as mentioned above) reveals no signal for synaptotagmin VI in the synaptic vesicles.\nThis finding is consistent with the absence of synaptotagmin VI on SV as reported by Takamori, S et al (Cell, 2006)\n\n6/2/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Experimental procedures:\nSubcellular Fractionations-Rat brain homogenates were subfractionated\ninto crude synaptic vesicles, mitochondria, myelin, and synaptic\nplasma membranes by the method of Jones and Matus (27)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1145" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

